  "response_text": "To calculate the eigenvalues of the matrix [[4, -2], [1, 1]], we need to find the values of \u03bb (lambda) that satisfy the characteristic equation:\n\n|A - \u03bbI| = 0\n\nwhere A is the given matrix, I is the identity matrix, and \u03bb is the eigenvalue.\n\nThe characteristic equation for the given matrix is:\n\n| [[4, -2], [1, 1]] - \u03bb [[1, 0], [0, 1]] | = 0\n\n| [[4-\u03bb, -2], [1, 1-\u03bb]] | = 0\n\nExpanding the determinant, we get:\n\n(4-\u03bb)(1-\u03bb) - (-2)(1) = 0\n\nSimplifying the equation, we get:\n\n(4-\u03bb)(1-\u03bb) + 2 = 0\n\nExpanding and simplifying further, we get:\n\n4 - 5\u03bb + \u03bb^",
